reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Fans, PWM helps a lot with noise!
reviews.reviewText: For those who do not know, PWM means that these fans have a 4-pin connector instead of a 3-pin connector. That 4th pin allows for your motherboard to control the speed of the fan depending on temperature (or custom if you tweak this in your BIOS or motherboard fan control software). This can help a lot with noise. With a 3-pin fan, it's going to run at full speed, all the time. With a 4-pin (and motherboard that supports it) it's going to run at whatever speed the motherboard thinks is necessary to keep things cool; usually slow under little/no load and fast as things heat up.These fans are quiet and work well. I recently used them in an Antec C80 case build for a blacked-out build and they look and work great!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good performing PWM fan with a reasonable price tag
reviews.reviewText: I got this "Okinos, 67CFM, 1500RPM, 4Pin PWM, Hurricane Series, 120mm Case Fan 5 Packs" to replace some of the 3-pin case fans I had. For 5 PWM fans, the price is very reasonable. They function well at the same time. I used the included hub to connect all my case fans with the fan header from the motherboard and was able to set a reasonable temperature curve. The fans are overall quiet, even at max speed.I'm very happy with this product so far and thus would recommend it. I hope you find this review helpful and I appreciate that.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good value fans for moving air through a case
reviews.reviewText: Thes fans aren't noise, they move a good amount of air, and they use standard PWM connectors. They would be great for moving air in and out of a computer case. It doesn't appear that the fan blade design would develop enough static pressure to work well with radiators.
